 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "76517784",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- definition and evaluation of the `non-linear rule 30` elementary cellular automata in $1D$,\n",
    "\n",
    "- transformation between spacetime- and diagonal- coordinates,\n",
    "\n",
    "- computation of the $m$-th right diagonal, \n",
    "\n",
    "- computation of the map $m \\mapsto [P_m, T_m, w_m]$ where $P_m=$ period, $T_m=$ preperiod, and $w_m=$ periodic word; of the $m$-th diagonal,\n",
    "\n",
    "- computing until `out of memory`, exhausting allocable memory.\n",
    "\n",
    "This dynamical system is believed to be `computationally irreducible`, which does not admit any simpler linear prediction than evolving the system directly, with complexity growing as $\\mathcal{O}(t^2)$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d3f9a132",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### local rule : $f(l,c,r)=l \\oplus  (c  \\lor  r) \\ \\implies \\ F : [0,1]^\\mathbb{Z} \\to [0,1]^\\mathbb{Z}$\n",
    " \n",
    "- $\\oplus=$ XOR gate, and $\\lor=$ OR gate.\n",
    " \n",
    "- evolution from a single seed $(\\cdots 00100 \\cdots)$. "
    " \n",
    "- crossref: [OEIS-A364773](https://oeis.org/A364773) "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "31b3e4ac",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def cellular_automaton_rule30_numpy(t_steps):\n",
    "    width = 2 * t_steps + 1\n",
    "    center = width // 2\n",
    "\n",
    "    ca = np.zeros((t_steps + 1, width), dtype=np.uint8)\n",
    "    ca[0, center] = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    for t in range(t_steps):\n",
    "        left   = np.roll(ca[t], 1)\n",
    "        center = ca[t]\n",
    "        right  = np.roll(ca[t], -1)\n",
    "\n",
    "        left[0] = 0\n",
    "        right[-1] = 0\n",
    "\n",
    "        neighborhood = (left << 2) | (center << 1) | right\n",
    "        ca[t + 1] = (30 >> neighborhood) & 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    return ca\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def LeftDiagonal(t0, x0, length):\n",
    "    ca = cellular_automaton_rule30_numpy(t0 + length)\n",
    "    center = ca.shape[1] // 2\n",
    "\n",
    "    return ca[\n",
    "        np.arange(t0, t0 + length),\n",
    "        center + x0 - np.arange(length)\n",
    "    ].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def RightDiagonal(t0, x0, length):\n",
    "    ca = cellular_automaton_rule30_numpy(t0 + length)\n",
    "    center = ca.shape[1] // 2\n",
    "\n",
    "    return ca[\n",
    "        np.arange(t0, t0 + length),\n",
    "        center + x0 + np.arange(length)\n",
    "    ].tolist()\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "8e7ce287",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from typing import Iterable, Dict, Union\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def detect_ultimate_periodicity(\n",
    "    seq: Iterable[int],\n",
    "    *,\n",
    "    max_period: int | None = None\n",
    ") -> Union[str, Dict[str, object]]:\n",
    "    seq = tuple(seq)\n",
    "    n = len(seq)\n",
    "\n",
    "    if not all(x in (0, 1) for x in seq):\n",
    "        raise ValueError(\"Sequence must be binary (0/1 only).\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    if max_period is None:\n",
    "        max_period = n // 2\n",
    "\n",
    "    for mu in range(n):\n",
    "        for p in range(1, min(max_period, n - mu) + 1):\n",
    "            valid = True\n",
    "            for i in range(mu, n - p):\n",
    "                if seq[i] != seq[i + p]:\n",
    "                    valid = False\n",
    "                    break\n",
    "\n",
    "            if valid:\n",
    "                periodic_word = seq[mu:mu + p]\n",
    "                return {\n",
    "                    \"preperiod\": mu,\n",
    "                    \"period\": p,\n",
    "                    \"periodic_word\": periodic_word,\n",
    "                }\n",
    "\n",
    "    return \"aperiodic w.r.t. the given length\"\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "a8ef378c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
      "left-diagonal starting at (t= 16, x= 16) with length= 1000\n",
      "--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
      "\n",
      "period = 8\n",
      "preperiod = 20\n",
      "periodic word = (0, 1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 1, 0)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def periodicity_analysis(starting_time = int, starting_cell = int, length = int, side = str):\n",
    "    if side == \"left\":\n",
    "        seq = LeftDiagonal(starting_time, starting_cell, length)\n",
    "    elif side == \"right\":\n",
    "        seq = RightDiagonal(starting_time, starting_cell, length)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print('--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------')\n",
    "    print(f\"{side}-diagonal starting at (t= {starting_time}, x= {starting_cell}) with length= {length}\")\n",
    "    print('--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\\n')\n",
    "    period_detection_res = detect_ultimate_periodicity(seq)\n",
    "\n",
    "    print(f'period = {period_detection_res[\"period\"]}')\n",
    "    print(f'preperiod = {period_detection_res[\"preperiod\"]}')\n",
    "    print(f'periodic word = {period_detection_res[\"periodic_word\"]}')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return None\n",
    "\n",
    "periodicity_analysis(16, 16, 1000,\"left\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ab54ee63",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6adbe0c3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The pattern for $ m \\geq 2 $ is:\n",
    "\n",
    "- For even $ m = 2n $: $(x_0, t_0) = (-n, \\, n-1)$\n",
    "- For odd $ m = 2n+1 $: $(x_0, t_0) = (-(n+1), \\, n-1)$\n",
    "\n",
    "This can be expressed uniformly as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$x_0 = -\\left\\lceil \\frac{m}{2} \\right\\rceil, \\quad t_0 = \\left\\lfloor \\frac{m}{2} \\right\\rfloor - 1$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c255874d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "$m \\to (x_0, t_0)$\n",
    "\n",
    "-----------------\n",
    "\n",
    "2 -> (-1, 0)\n",
    "3 -> (-2, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "4 -> (-2, 1)\n",
    "5 -> (-3, 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "6 -> (-3, 2)\n",
    "7 -> (-4, 2)\n",
    "\n",
    "8 -> (-4, 3)\n",
    "9 -> (-5, 3)\n",
    "\n",
    "10 -> (-5, 4)\n",
    "11 -> (-6, 4)\n",
    "\n",
    "12 -> (-6, 5)\n",
    "13 -> (-7, 5)\n",
    "\n",
    "14 -> (-7, 6)\n",
    "15 -> (-8, 6)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "3ee24f26",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
